This fact contains one row for each interaction that we have with a customer/contact, e.g. a call using Amazon Connect. Note- May not involve direct contact with a human from Trustpower, e.g. an unanswered call. Also note if call transferred to another agent that is treated as another interaction. Source- h_interaction, l_interaction_is_via_communication_channel, l_interaction_is_from_communication_source, l_interaction_can_be_via_team_member, s_interactions_details

Connection point for a service. Currently, loading data from READ_DATA_EMDM and available_services__c.

Interaction between a team member and a contact/account. For sales, can be in relation to a lead or an opportunity. Otherwise can be any customer interaction. For sales, data is recieved from Task and for Connect, AMAZON_CONNECT.CONTACT_TRACE_RECORD.

An Interaction Component is a single transaction within an interaction - a line of a webchat conversation, a phrase on phone call, a script on an IVR system, Answering a call. When the conversation passes to the next person (from customer to agent and back again, or from one step in the phone menu to the next), it moves to the next Interaction Component. All conversation logs will eventually be stored against this object. Data is recieved from AMAZON_CONNECT.CONTACT_FLOW_LOG where prompt_text is not null.

Anywhere we can a) sell utilities to or b) sign up utilities for. Source, salesforce.location__c. Frequency of data, not often, but can happen - agent can create if not known on inbound. Can remove decommission, can update.
The energy meter. For EMDM this comes from READ_DATA_EMDM view.
The channel on a meter. For EMDM this comes from READ_DATA_EMDM.
This relationship is found in the SYS_EMDM_ENRICHED.READ_DATA_EMDM. It should include any -1 interval_length reads.
A Market Proposition, with special conditions attached, and an incentive for signing. Source, salesforce.offer_type__c. Frequency of data, every few months.

From a sales perspective, this is the Record of Bundle. A Quote is a ‘controller’ for an order - if the quote changes, the order will change. Source, salesforce.order. Frequency of data, should usually be daily (Sunday, holiday exception).
From a sales perspective, a single item on an order. Source, salesforce.orderitem. Frequency of data should usually be daily (Sunday, holiday exception).

In the sales context, a quote is document provided to a prospect that states a price for goods and services. Source, salesforce.sbqq__quote__c. Frequency of data usually every day but with exceptions (holiday etc).

In the sales context, a quote line is a particular line item on a quote for a single good or service. Source, salesforce.sbqq__quoteline__c. Frequency of data should usually be daily (Sunday, holiday exception).
Source, salesforce.location__c. Frequencyof data, unlikely to change much.

This comes from the READ_DATA_STATUS_EMDM and READ_DATA_EMDM joined on filename and reading status. It only holds interval usage reads (interval_length != -1). This ensemble holds revisions of usage readings. It is at meter channel, date time and revision level. The usage amount for a set meter channel at day/time could be recieved more than once. Each time is a new revision of the usage and will come with a new filename.
The details of the service supplied. Source=SYS_GTV.EMSUTILITY (GENEMSUTILITY) and UTIL_GROUP

This details hold an instance of a usage read. It is at meter channel and date/time level. This doesn't hold the actual usage amount as that is at a lower level which includes the revision of the usage reading. This comes from the read_data_emdm and only includes data with interval_length != -1.

The secure data for the history of usage. This comes from the READ_DATA_STATUS_EMDM and READ_DATA_EMDM joined on filename and reading status. It only holds the interval usage reads. (interval_length != -1) This ensemble holds revisions of usage readings. It is a at meter channel, date time and revision level. The usage amount for a set meter channel at day/time could be recieved more than once. Each time is a new revision of the usage and will come with a new filename.

An account is a billing entity, and represents a collection of one or more services, some of which may be bundled together. Note- An account is created in Salesforce, for prospects who are not yet signed up. Source Table= SYS_GTV.ACCOUNTS (View GENACCOUNTS)

The most granular charge of a product/service. Sourced currently in gendebt - will be able to replace some grouped areas (eg phone calls) with individual rows in future. DEBT and debt_arc tables provide the data for this Only load records that have dinvoiceref is not null
A billing statement that is sent to the account holder. GBSTATEMENT union GBSTATEMENTHIST1+2+3+4
A financial transaction on an account - a charge or a payment/credit. GTV source views GENDEBT & GENDEBT_ARC (archive of GENDEBT) (tables DEBT, DEBT_ARC)

The association usually of a charge and a payment. Can be many to many, e.g. a charge can be paid off over time via multiple payments, and a payment can be for multiple charges. Populated from DEBT_RECEIPT (View GENDEBT_RECEIPT)

A way of tracking different types of transactions including the payment method for payments. Source= join from SYS_GTV.EMS_TRANS_CODES to SYS_GTV.EMS_ANCODE using GL_ANCODE (VIews GENEMS_TRANS_CODES, GENEMS_ANCODE)
An activity that can be undertaken by a team member. Data is received from AMAZON_CONNECT.AGENT_EVENT_CLEAN

The means by which we contact or are contacted by a customer or prospect/sales lead? e.g. door knocking, phone out, phone in, website, direct mail. Will be populating from a number of sources. For Sales, source is Opportunity. For Amazon Connect, source is contact_trace_record. Frequency of data is reasonably static.
